WEBVTT

00:03.291 --> 00:05.083
♪ OHHH OHHH OHHH ♪

00:07.542 --> 00:09.083
PREVIOUSLY
ON "PRIVATE PRACTICE"...

00:09.125 --> 00:10.792
I'M GETTING MARRIED.
TO WHOM?

00:10.834 --> 00:13.041
TO CHARLOTTE.
YOU ARE NOT MARRYING HER.

00:13.083 --> 00:16.041
IF ANYTHING
EVER HAPPENED TO ME...

00:16.083 --> 00:18.417
(monitor beeping erratically)

00:18.458 --> 00:21.458
(monitor emitting
continuous tone)

00:24.500 --> 00:27.166
WHAT ARE YOU EVEN DOING HERE?
YOU DON'T HAVE A JOB,

00:27.208 --> 00:29.041
BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT
TO TALK TO YOUR BROTHER,

00:29.083 --> 00:30.834
YET YOU'RE GIVING ME ADVICE
ON MY LIFE?

00:30.875 --> 00:33.041
DEAL WITH YOUR OWN MESS
BEFORE YOU GET INTO MINE.

00:33.083 --> 00:35.125
MAYA'S IN LABOR.
OH, SHE'S IN LABOR.

00:35.166 --> 00:38.959
NAOMI, SOMETHING HAS HAPPENED
TO MAYA.

00:39.000 --> 00:42.125
MAYA'S FINE. SHE'S OUT NOW,
BUT SHE'S DOING GREAT.

00:42.166 --> 00:44.875
(Addison)
YOU HAVE A BEAUTIFUL BABY GIRL.

00:44.917 --> 00:46.542
SHE'S READY...

00:46.583 --> 00:49.041
FOR YOU.

00:49.083 --> 00:51.041
SHE LOVES YOU
AND YOU LOVE HER.

00:55.834 --> 00:59.000
(The Black Keys' "Your Touch"
playing)

01:05.041 --> 01:08.041
♪ AND I WANT ♪

01:08.083 --> 01:12.792
♪ AND YOU GOT IT ♪

01:12.834 --> 01:15.000
♪ SO MUCH ♪

01:16.625 --> 01:19.041
♪ I'M CRAZY FOR ♪

01:19.083 --> 01:20.583
♪ YOUR TOUCH ♪

01:20.625 --> 01:22.583
OH, CHARLOTTE,
I FORGOT TO TELL YOU,

01:22.625 --> 01:24.041
A SPRING WEDDING--NO GO.

01:24.083 --> 01:27.041
MY MOTHER REMINDED ME--
ALLERGIES.
IT'LL BE A CONVERSATION.

01:27.083 --> 01:29.041
♪ YOUR TOUCH ♪

01:29.083 --> 01:32.041
OH!
PETE, WE'RE GONNA WAKE
THE BABY.

01:32.083 --> 01:34.667
HE'S A HEAVY SLEEPER.
HE'S NOT DEAF. (laughs)

01:34.709 --> 01:35.875
(laughs)

01:35.917 --> 01:37.417
♪♪♪

01:37.458 --> 01:39.625
AS LONG AS WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT YOUR MOTHER,

01:39.667 --> 01:42.041
TELL HER MY PASTOR
WANTS TO TALK TO HER RABBI

01:42.083 --> 01:44.041
BEFORE HE AGREES TO STAND
UNDER THAT CIRCUS TENT.

01:44.083 --> 01:45.667
IT'S CALLED A CHUPPAH.

01:45.709 --> 01:48.834
WAIT. YOU WERE SERIOUS ABOUT
HAVING YOUR PASTOR THERE?

01:48.875 --> 01:50.417
COOPER.

01:50.458 --> 01:52.250
♪♪♪

01:52.291 --> 01:54.041
OW!

01:54.083 --> 01:57.041
"OW" BAD?
"OW" GOOD.

01:57.083 --> 02:00.250
SO ARE WE, UH...

02:00.291 --> 02:02.875
DONE? OH, YEAH.

02:02.917 --> 02:04.333
(Violet sighs)
(Pete) ARE YOU--

02:04.375 --> 02:06.291
ARE YOU--
SO GOOD.

02:06.333 --> 02:09.500
♪♪♪

02:13.500 --> 02:15.291
WE SHOULD GET READY.

02:15.333 --> 02:18.542
♪♪♪

02:20.709 --> 02:24.041
(both panting)

02:24.083 --> 02:33.458
WE SHOULD GET MARRIED.

02:33.500 --> 02:35.041
HEY.

02:35.083 --> 02:36.583
YOU LOOK TIRED.

02:36.625 --> 02:38.500
EXHAUSTED.

02:38.542 --> 02:41.333
WELL, I'M FLYING BACK AND FORTH
TO SEE WILLIAM,

02:41.375 --> 02:43.333
FIFE QUIT,
AND YOUR GRANDCHILD

02:43.375 --> 02:46.041
DOESN'T EXACTLY
LIKE TO SLEEP AT NIGHT, SO--
I TOLD YOU THEY
COULD STAY WITH ME.

02:46.083 --> 02:48.041
WELL, MAYA'S ON BED REST,
AND SHE WANTS TO BE

02:48.083 --> 02:50.208
IN HER OWN BED
IN HER OWN ROOM.

02:50.250 --> 02:53.208
IT'S FINE. I'M JUST GONNA
BE TIRED FOR A WHILE.
WHY DON'T WE GET DINK
TO COME OVER AND HELP OUT?

02:53.250 --> 02:55.291
OKAY, YEAH. IF I NEED
MY GUITAR RESTRUNG,

02:55.333 --> 02:58.291
I'LL BE SURE AND CALL DINK,
BUT OLIVIA--
OLIVIA IS HIS DAUGHTER.
MAYA IS HIS WIFE.

02:58.333 --> 03:01.291
AND IT'S ABOUT TIME THEY START
DEPENDING ON HIM AND NOT YOU.

03:01.333 --> 03:04.542
I AM NOT READY FOR THAT.
NEITHER IS HE, SO...

03:04.583 --> 03:06.625
NAI, DINK IS--
DINK IS A BOY.

03:06.667 --> 03:09.041
AND THIS IS MAN'S WORK.
NO.

03:10.875 --> 03:13.041
HELLO.

03:13.083 --> 03:15.291
HI.

03:16.792 --> 03:20.250
OKAY, DO NOT EVEN THINK...

03:20.291 --> 03:22.250
ABOUT SMOKING THIS.

03:22.291 --> 03:24.542
ONE QUICK ONE BEFORE WE G--
SINCE WHEN
DID YOU START SMOKING?

03:24.583 --> 03:26.792
SINCE DEREK TOOK A BULLET
TO THE CHEST.
AMELIA--

03:26.834 --> 03:29.583
NO, I AM NOT GOING TO SEATTLE.
HE WON'T EVEN RETURN MY CALLS.

03:29.625 --> 03:32.125
HE DOES NOT WANT TO SEE ME.
YOU'RE AFRAID.

03:32.166 --> 03:34.959
UH, YOU PASSED
ON A RELATIONSHIP WITH SAM,

03:35.000 --> 03:36.959
WHO IS BASICALLY PERFECT,
BECAUSE YOU WERE AFRAID.

03:37.000 --> 03:38.875
I MEAN, YOU GUYS
DON'T EVEN SPEAK ANYMORE,

03:38.917 --> 03:41.291
SO YOU CAN SAVE
THE THERAPY TALK.
GIVE.

03:41.333 --> 03:43.375
GIVE!

03:43.417 --> 03:45.000
(package crinkles)

03:48.291 --> 03:51.208
I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THE STONE.

03:51.250 --> 03:54.792
GRAY SEEMED... ELEGANT.
IS IT TOO DULL?

03:54.834 --> 03:57.041
BECAUSE I CAN GET THEM
TO DO ANOTHER ONE.

03:57.083 --> 03:58.792
(Cooper) IT'S NICE.
IT IS.

03:58.834 --> 04:00.792
YOU DID A GREAT JOB.
DELL WOULD'VE LIKED IT.

04:00.834 --> 04:03.041
YEAH, DELL WOULD'VE LIKED
THAT WE'RE ALL HERE TOGETHER

04:03.083 --> 04:06.083
FOR THE UNVEILING.
I CAN'T BELIEVE WE'RE HERE,
WE'RE DOING THIS.

04:06.125 --> 04:09.041
I CAN'T BELIEVE DELL IS DEAD.
I KNOW.

04:09.083 --> 04:12.000
DELL IS DEAD. WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON WITH THE WORLD?

04:12.041 --> 04:14.000
I WAS JUST THINKING
THE SAME THING

04:14.041 --> 04:16.333
ABOUT WILLIAM
THIS PAST WEEK.

04:16.375 --> 04:18.667
I MEAN, HE'S DYING. HOW COULD IT
BE THAT WILLIAM IS DYING?

04:18.709 --> 04:22.041
HOW COULD IT BE THAT MAYA
GOT HIT BY A DRUNK DRIVER?

04:22.083 --> 04:23.667
MY CHILD?

04:23.709 --> 04:26.208
YEAH, WELL, MY BROTHER GOT SHOT
BY A CRAZED GUNMAN.

04:26.250 --> 04:28.208
I MEAN,
THE WORLD'S A CRAPPY PLACE.

04:28.250 --> 04:30.041
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL HEADSTONE,
THOUGH.

04:30.083 --> 04:32.041
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

04:33.792 --> 04:35.917
PETE AND I
ARE GETTING MARRIED.

04:35.959 --> 04:39.458
I KNOW. MAYBE I SHOULDN'T
HAVE SAID ANYTHING YET.

04:39.500 --> 04:41.041
BUT... (laughs)

04:41.083 --> 04:45.041
I-I THOUGHT WE COULD USE
SOME HAPPY NEWS.

04:45.083 --> 04:46.125
(laughs)

04:46.166 --> 04:47.458
(chuckles)

04:47.500 --> 04:50.792
(Naomi) YOU GUYS...
(Sam) OKAY.

04:50.834 --> 04:53.333
(Addison) WOW.
(Charlotte) CONGRATS.

04:53.375 --> 04:57.291
(all speaking indistinctly)

05:01.291 --> 05:03.792
(Violet) IT JUST HAPPENED
THIS MORNING.

05:03.834 --> 05:06.542
PETE SUGGESTED IT,
AND, UH, IT SEEMED RIGHT,

05:06.583 --> 05:10.041
SO WE DECIDED TO GO FOR IT.

05:10.083 --> 05:12.000
SAY SOMETHING.

05:12.041 --> 05:13.875
SPEAK WORDS.

05:13.917 --> 05:16.750
OKAY, JUST HOLD--YEAH,
GIVE--GIVE ME A--I NEED A...

05:16.792 --> 05:19.750
OKAY, LOOK. FRIEND COOPER
WANTS TO GIVE YOU A BIG HUG.

05:19.792 --> 05:21.375
BUT OBJECTIVE COOPER...

05:21.417 --> 05:23.375
THINK THIS MIGHT BE
A LITTLE TOO FAST.

05:23.417 --> 05:25.834
FRIEND COOPER FIRST.
OKAY.

05:25.875 --> 05:27.500
(laughs) OKAY.
CONGRATULATIONS.

05:27.542 --> 05:30.083
I AM SO HAPPY FOR YOU.
THANK YOU.

05:30.125 --> 05:32.834
AND TELL OBJECTIVE COOPER
THAT IT'S NOT LIKE

05:32.875 --> 05:35.041
I NEED A BIG FLOOFY WHITE DRESS
OR A WEDDING MARCH.

05:35.083 --> 05:38.083
ALL I NEED IS PETE
AND THE PEOPLE I LOVE AROUND ME,

05:38.125 --> 05:40.166
AND I CAN HAVE THAT NOW.
WHEN YOU SAY "NOW," YOU MEAN--

05:40.208 --> 05:43.083
THIS WEEKEND.
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

05:43.125 --> 05:45.417
THERE'S NO REASON TO WAIT.
THERE ARE MANY REASONS
TO WAIT.

05:45.458 --> 05:47.291
NAME ONE.
WELL, I MEAN, YOUR--
YOUR PARENTS

05:47.333 --> 05:50.917
AREN'T JUST GONNA
HOP ON A PLANE.
THAT'S RANDOM, AND I SAID
"PEOPLE I LOVE."

05:50.959 --> 05:53.291
OKAY, HOW ABOUT THE FACT
THAT A COUPLE OF MONTHS AGO,

05:53.333 --> 05:56.041
YOU TWO WERE AT EACH OTHER'S
THROATS IN A COURTROOM?
WE'RE PAST THAT.

05:56.083 --> 05:58.750
HOW FAR PAST?
FAR ENOUGH.

05:58.792 --> 06:00.750
AND TELL OBJECTIVE COOPER

06:00.792 --> 06:02.750
THAT IF HE KEEPS ANNOYING ME
ABOUT THIS,

06:02.792 --> 06:06.375
I'M NOT GONNA ASK FRIEND COOPER
TO BE MY MAID OF HONOR.

06:07.792 --> 06:09.542
(Charlotte)
TAKE DEEP BREATHS, RYAN.

06:09.583 --> 06:11.041
(panting) IT'S DIFFICULT.

06:11.083 --> 06:13.583
6 LITERS OF O-2
AND HANG DOPAMINE.
WHAT'S HAPPENING TO ME?

06:13.625 --> 06:15.583
YOU'VE DEVELOPED
A CARDIOMYOPATHY

06:15.625 --> 06:17.417
SECONDARY TO THE DIALYSIS.
YOU'RE IN HEART FAILURE.

06:17.458 --> 06:19.333
THESE MEDS SHOULD STABILIZE YOU
RIGHT AWAY.

06:19.375 --> 06:21.750
AND MY KIDNEYS?
COMPLETELY SHUT DOWN.

06:21.792 --> 06:23.417
DR. BENNETT
ALREADY PUT YOUR NAME

06:23.458 --> 06:25.417
ON THE TRANSPLANT
WAITING LIST.

06:25.458 --> 06:27.417
YEAH? I'LL BE LONG DEAD
BEFORE SOME MORON

06:27.458 --> 06:30.041
CRASHES HIS MOTORCYCLE INTO
A TREE, AND I GET HIS KIDNEY.

06:30.083 --> 06:33.041
REMEMBER OUR TALK ABOUT
BEING MORE POSITIVE?
SCREW POSITIVE.

06:33.083 --> 06:35.041
I'M AN IMPOSSIBLE MATCH
WITH THE ANTIBODIES FROM

06:35.083 --> 06:37.375
MY PREVIOUS BLOOD TRANSFUSION,
AND YOU KNOW IT.

06:37.417 --> 06:40.667
YOU'D HAVE A BETTER CHANCE WITH
A KIDNEY FROM A FAMILY MEMBER.

06:40.709 --> 06:42.041
I'M NOT CALLING HIM.

06:42.083 --> 06:44.041
A KIDNEY FROM YOUR BROTHER

06:44.083 --> 06:47.000
WOULD DECREASE THE CHANCE
OF REJECTION BY 90%.

06:47.041 --> 06:49.166
(exhales deeply)

06:49.208 --> 06:51.375
I GOT A BETTER IDEA.

06:51.417 --> 06:54.166
SAVE YOUR SPEECH. DR. BENNETT
ALREADY TOLD ME YOU TRIED

06:54.208 --> 06:57.000
TO BUY YOUR WAY TO THE TOP OF
THE TRANSPLANT LIST LAST WEEK.

06:57.041 --> 06:59.375
WELL, I OFFERED HIM A NEW
M.R.I. FOR THE HOSPITAL.

06:59.417 --> 07:01.417
AND FOR YOU?

07:01.458 --> 07:05.417
HOW ABOUT A NEW SPORTS CAR?

07:05.458 --> 07:06.834
(exhales deeply)

07:06.875 --> 07:08.834
WHERE'S YOUR SENSE OF HUMOR,
DR. KING?

07:08.875 --> 07:10.625
I SEE NOTHING FUNNY
IN YOU DYING.

07:10.667 --> 07:12.208
CALL YOUR BROTHER

07:12.250 --> 07:15.041
AND TELL HIM YOU NEED HIS KIDNEY
TO SAVE YOUR LIFE.

07:15.083 --> 07:16.417
(sighs)

07:16.458 --> 07:18.083
ALL RIGHT.

07:18.125 --> 07:19.542
I'LL CALL HIM.

07:19.583 --> 07:22.041
SO... WE WANT IT TO BE
OUR EMBRYO

07:22.083 --> 07:24.041
CARRIED BY A SURROGATE.
(Naomi) YEAH.

07:24.083 --> 07:27.917
GIVEN KENDRA'S HISTORY WITH
LUPUS, THAT'S A GOOD OPTION.

07:27.959 --> 07:30.333
THERE ARE
A FEW POTENTIAL ISSUES.
WE'VE USED A SURROGATE BEFORE.

07:30.375 --> 07:35.917
OH. UH, IT--IT SAYS HERE
THAT YOU HAVE NO CHILDREN.

07:35.959 --> 07:38.125
WE LOST OUR SON.

07:38.166 --> 07:40.041
OH, I'M SORRY.

07:40.083 --> 07:42.875
HIS NAME WAS MAX,
AND HE WAS 5 MONTHS OLD.

07:42.917 --> 07:45.500
HE HAD JUST STARTED
TO SIT UP.

07:45.542 --> 07:47.041
HE WOULD SMILE

07:47.083 --> 07:49.542
WHEN EITHER ONE OF US
WOULD COME INTO THE ROOM.

07:49.583 --> 07:52.083
BUT JUST US,
WHICH MADE US FEEL LIKE...

07:52.125 --> 07:53.875
(exhales)

07:53.917 --> 07:57.041
(voice breaks)
AND THEN HE WAS GONE.

07:57.083 --> 08:00.417
(normal voice)
PLEASE, DR. BENNETT...

08:00.458 --> 08:02.000
HELP US.

08:03.750 --> 08:05.250
(footsteps approach)

08:05.291 --> 08:07.792
YOU WANT TO HEAR SOMETHING
INCREDIBLY SAD?
WHO SAYS YES TO THAT?

08:07.834 --> 08:09.959
I'M GONNA TELL YOU ANYWAY.
THIS COUPLE I JUST SAW

08:10.000 --> 08:12.041
LOST THEIR BABY
AT 5 MONTHS OLD.

08:12.083 --> 08:14.125
OH.
AND THEY'RE DESPERATE
TO HAVE ANOTHER ONE,

08:14.166 --> 08:18.333
AND HIS SPERM COUNT IS FINE,
AND GIVEN HER AGE

08:18.375 --> 08:20.333
AND HER OVARIAN RESERVE,
I MEAN...

08:20.375 --> 08:22.959
"KENDRA WALKER"?

08:23.000 --> 08:25.500
IS HER HUSBAND NAMED DAVE?

08:25.542 --> 08:27.834
YEAH. YOU KNOW THEM?

08:27.875 --> 08:30.208
YEAH. I WAS IN THE E.R.
WHEN THEIR BABY CAME IN.

08:30.250 --> 08:32.709
THE FATHER
LEFT HIM IN THE CAR,

08:32.750 --> 08:34.542
AND HE SUFFOCATED TO DEATH.

08:36.959 --> 08:38.709
GOOD. MR. MASON, YOU'RE HERE.

08:38.750 --> 08:41.291
GIVEN THE SEVERITY
OF YOUR BROTHER'S CONDITION,

08:41.333 --> 08:44.792
WE'D NEED TO DO THE TRANSPLANT
AS QUICKLY AS POSSIBLE.
DR. KING--

08:44.834 --> 08:46.458
WE JUST NEED A BASIC WORKUP,

08:46.500 --> 08:49.458
AND WE COULD HAVE YOU UNDER
THE KNIFE IN THE NEXT 24 HOURS.
DR. KING.

08:49.500 --> 08:52.041
I UNDERSTAND THIS MUST BE
A LOT TO TAKE IN,

08:52.083 --> 08:54.041
BUT IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS,

08:54.083 --> 08:56.792
WE'D BE HAPPY
TO TALK ABOUT THEM.

08:56.834 --> 08:58.625
WHAT DO THESE TUBES DO?

09:01.166 --> 09:03.333
THE BIG ONES CARRY THE BLOOD
TO BE FILTERED,

09:03.375 --> 09:06.250
AND THE SMALL ONES
CARRY THE CARDIAC MEDS.

09:06.291 --> 09:11.458
KEVIN, DO YOU KNOW
WHY YOU'RE HERE TODAY?

09:11.500 --> 09:14.000
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

09:14.041 --> 09:16.000
YEAH, MY BIG BROTHER
NEEDS MY HELP.

09:16.041 --> 09:17.583
RIGHT, RYAN?

09:17.625 --> 09:19.500
THAT'S RIGHT, BUDDY.

09:19.542 --> 09:21.917
YAY. I GET TO HELP.

09:28.083 --> 09:32.041
HEY, HE'S A LITTLE SLOW,
BUT HE'S ALL RIGHT.

09:32.083 --> 09:34.709
HE CAN DRESS HIMSELF.
HE GOES TO THE STORE.

09:34.750 --> 09:36.792
HE HAS FRIENDS.
WHERE DOES HE LIVE?

09:36.834 --> 09:39.000
IN A KIND OF, UH,
GROUP HOME OR SOMETHING.

09:39.041 --> 09:41.375
BUT YOU'RE NOT SURE.
LOOK, I PAY FOR IT.

09:41.417 --> 09:43.041
YOU KNOW, HE'S HAPPY

09:43.083 --> 09:46.041
LIVING WITH OTHER PEOPLE
JUST LIKE HIM, OKAY?

09:46.083 --> 09:48.083
I DON'T SEE HIM THAT OFTEN.
WELL, GIVEN HIS MENTAL STATE,

09:48.125 --> 09:50.041
I CAN UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU HAD QUALMS

09:50.083 --> 09:52.500
ASKING HIM
TO DONATE A KIDNEY.

09:52.542 --> 09:55.458
I HAD QUALMS CALLING HIM
BECAUSE KEVIN IS NEEDY.

09:55.500 --> 09:58.750
YOU HAVE TO EXPLAIN EVERYTHING
A THOUSAND TIMES.

09:58.792 --> 10:00.750
HE GETS SO EMOTIONAL.
IT'S JUST...

10:00.792 --> 10:02.250
IT'S EXHAUSTING.

10:02.291 --> 10:04.417
NOW YOU'LL BE
JUST SWEET ENOUGH

10:04.458 --> 10:07.041
THAT HE'LL AGREE
TO GIVE YOU A KIDNEY.
WELL, THAT'S WHAT YOU
TOLD ME TO DO, DR. KING.

10:07.083 --> 10:10.041
AND THE TRUTH IS,
I WON'T HAVE TO BE THAT SWEET.

10:10.083 --> 10:11.959
KEVIN IDOLIZES ME.

10:12.000 --> 10:14.041
HE'LL DO ANYTHING FOR ME.

10:14.083 --> 10:17.041
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

10:17.083 --> 10:19.041
DR. BENNETT WANTED US TO TALK.

10:19.083 --> 10:21.458
TO MAKE SURE WE'RE READY
TO HAVE ANOTHER BABY.

10:21.500 --> 10:23.041
WE GET IT.

10:23.083 --> 10:25.041
WELL, WE'D ALSO
LIKE TO UNDERSTAND

10:25.083 --> 10:28.041
WHY YOU DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT HOW YOUR SON DIED

10:28.083 --> 10:30.166
WHEN YOU FIRST CAME IN.

10:30.208 --> 10:32.750
PEOPLE LOOK AT YOU DIFFERENT

10:32.792 --> 10:34.792
WHEN THEY KNOW.

10:34.834 --> 10:36.709
THEY JUDGE.

10:36.750 --> 10:39.709
BUT WE'RE GOOD PARENTS,
AND WE'D LIKE TO BE AGAIN.

10:39.750 --> 10:41.709
I HAVE NO DOUBT
YOU COULD BE GOOD PARENTS.

10:41.750 --> 10:44.750
WHAT I'D LIKE TO UNDERSTAND
IS HOW YOU GRIEVED HIS DEATH.

10:44.792 --> 10:47.333
HOW WE...

10:47.375 --> 10:49.625
HOW? UH...

10:51.834 --> 10:54.041
I DON'T KNOW HOW.

10:54.083 --> 10:55.542
THERE IS NO HOW.

10:55.583 --> 10:57.834
LIKE THERE'S A WAY TO GRIEVE.

10:57.875 --> 11:00.208
THERE'S NO WAY. YOU JUST...

11:03.417 --> 11:06.041
KENDRA TOOK MAX TO DAYCARE...

11:06.083 --> 11:08.583
EVERY DAY.

11:08.625 --> 11:11.041
THAT MORNING, SHE WASN'T
FEELING WELL. SHE HAD THE FLU.

11:11.083 --> 11:14.959
SO SHE ASKED... ME
TO TAKE MAX.

11:17.125 --> 11:19.709
WHEN I GET BEHIND THE WHEEL
IN THE MORNING,

11:19.750 --> 11:21.500
I ALWAYS DO THE SAME THING--

11:21.542 --> 11:23.500
BRIEFCASE ON THE SEAT,
COFFEE IN THE CUP HOLDER,

11:23.542 --> 11:25.041
TURN ON PUBLIC RADIO.

11:25.083 --> 11:28.083
LATER, I LEARNED THERE'S
A THING CALLED AUTOPILOT.

11:28.125 --> 11:29.750
(mouths word)

11:29.792 --> 11:31.125
YOU DO SOMETHING ENOUGH,

11:31.166 --> 11:33.125
YOU DON'T EVEN
THINK ABOUT IT ANYMORE.

11:33.166 --> 11:35.166
YOU DON'T EVEN
NOTICE IT ANYMORE.

11:36.917 --> 11:39.750
AND THAT'S WHAT I DID.

11:39.792 --> 11:42.333
I WENT INTO AUTOPILOT.

11:42.375 --> 11:46.959
ONE MINUTE I WAS
TURNING ON PUBLIC RADIO...

11:47.000 --> 11:50.000
AND THE NEXT,
I WAS IN MY OFFICE.

11:54.583 --> 11:57.333
THE CAR SEAT...

11:57.375 --> 12:01.625
THEY MAKE 'EM
SO THEY FACE BACKWARD...

12:01.667 --> 12:04.792
(voice breaking)
AND HE WAS SLEEPING.

12:04.834 --> 12:08.750
I DIDN'T HEAR HIM,
COULDN'T SEE HIM.

12:11.917 --> 12:17.000
I WAS SITTING AT MY COMPUTER,
LATE FOR A STAFF MEETING.

12:17.041 --> 12:19.500
IT WAS LUNCHTIME.

12:21.083 --> 12:23.583
AND THEN MY...

12:23.625 --> 12:26.792
SCREENSAVER POPPED UP.

12:26.834 --> 12:31.208
(voice breaking)
MAX'S FACE IS MY SCREENSAVER.

12:31.250 --> 12:34.041
AND I JUST... RAN.

12:34.083 --> 12:37.291
I RAN TO THE CAR.

12:37.333 --> 12:40.417
BUT... IT WAS SUMMER.

12:40.458 --> 12:43.458
IT WAS HOT, AND...

12:43.500 --> 12:45.041
(cries)

12:45.083 --> 12:47.041
(sobs)

12:49.083 --> 12:52.625
KENDRA, CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT THIS HAS BEEN LIKE FOR YOU?

12:52.667 --> 12:55.208
YOU'RE ASKING ME
IF I HATE MY HUSBAND?

12:55.250 --> 12:57.625
NO--

12:57.667 --> 12:59.709
I DON'T.

12:59.750 --> 13:01.083
I'M...

13:01.125 --> 13:03.041
NUMB OR SOMETHING.

13:03.083 --> 13:05.041
BUT YOU'VE STAYED
WITH YOUR HUSBAND,

13:05.083 --> 13:07.041
AND YOU WANT TO HAVE
ANOTHER CHILD.

13:07.083 --> 13:09.917
EITHER I TRY
TO START OVER OR...

13:09.959 --> 13:11.917
OR WHAT?

13:13.542 --> 13:16.750
I... DON'T KNOW.

13:21.917 --> 13:24.875
HE HAS NO IDEA WHAT
HIS BROTHER'S ASKING HIM TO DO,

13:24.917 --> 13:26.959
WHAT IT MEANS
TO UNDERGO A SURGERY,

13:27.000 --> 13:29.041
AND THEN THE RISK
OF HAVING ONLY ONE KIDNEY

13:29.083 --> 13:32.041
WITH A FAMILY HISTORY
OF NEPHROTIC DISEASE.
IF KEVIN'S I.Q.
WERE 20 POINTS HIGHER,

13:32.083 --> 13:34.291
WE WOULDN'T EVEN
BE HAVING THIS CONVERSATION.

13:34.333 --> 13:35.917
WE'D BE PRAISING HIM

13:35.959 --> 13:38.917
FOR PUTTING HIS FAMILY FIRST
AND DOING THE RIGHT THING.

13:38.959 --> 13:40.542
LOOK... (sighs)

13:40.583 --> 13:42.583
I'M NOT IN LOVE
WITH THIS IDEA,

13:42.625 --> 13:45.542
BUT INTELLIGENCE
HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH LOVE.

13:45.583 --> 13:48.000
AND I THINK
KEVIN UNDERSTANDS THAT.

13:48.041 --> 13:50.041
I THINK KEVIN LOVES HIS BROTHER
AND FEELS A RESPONSIBILITY

13:50.083 --> 13:51.834
TO HELP HIM.
IS IT LOVE?

13:51.875 --> 13:54.291
OR IS KEVIN JUST SO STARVED
FOR HIS BROTHER'S ATTENTION

13:54.333 --> 13:56.291
AFTER BEING DUMPED
INTO SOME GROUP HOME

13:56.333 --> 13:59.417
THE MINUTE THEIR PARENTS DIED
THAT HE'D DO ANYTHING FOR HIM?

13:59.458 --> 14:01.041
RYAN'S AN ASS, SAM.

14:01.083 --> 14:05.625
MAYBE, BUT DOES THAT MEAN HE
DOESN'T HAVE THE RIGHT TO LIVE?

14:09.083 --> 14:10.417
ADDISON?

14:10.458 --> 14:12.125
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

14:12.166 --> 14:14.709
HEY. YEAH, I'M... FINE.

14:14.750 --> 14:17.542
I DIDN'T KNOW HOW YOU FELT
ABOUT VIOLET AND ME.

14:17.583 --> 14:19.959
YOU LOOKED UPSET,
SO I TH--I THOUGHT--

14:20.000 --> 14:23.041
DEAD BABIES.
THAT'S WHY I LOOK...

14:23.083 --> 14:24.542
UH, CONGRATULATIONS.

14:24.583 --> 14:27.375
LOOK, I KNOW HOW MUCH YOU WANTED
THINGS TO WORK OUT WITH SAM.

14:27.417 --> 14:29.333
AND I WAS HOPING
THEY WOULD, TOO,

14:29.375 --> 14:30.959
ESPECIALLY
GIVEN ME AND VIOLET.

14:31.000 --> 14:32.959
IT WOULD'VE BEEN... NICE.
YEAH.

14:33.000 --> 14:34.458
WOULD'VE BEEN NICE.

14:34.500 --> 14:36.333
IF YOU EVER WANT TO TALK--

14:36.375 --> 14:37.959
TALKING TO YOU

14:38.000 --> 14:39.959
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN ME AND SAM?

14:40.000 --> 14:41.959
I'D RATHER
THINK ABOUT DEAD BABIES.

14:42.000 --> 14:43.667
BUT... THANK YOU.

14:43.709 --> 14:45.667
OKAY. I DON'T WANT THIS
TO SOUND PATRONIZING,

14:45.709 --> 14:49.041
BUT YOU ARE GONNA FIND
SOMEONE GREAT.

14:49.083 --> 14:51.083
YOU WILL.

14:59.208 --> 15:03.667
(keyboard keys clicking)

15:03.709 --> 15:06.291
I GOT YOUR MESSAGE,
DR. BENNETT.

15:06.333 --> 15:08.291
YOU SAID
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME.

15:08.333 --> 15:10.500
HAVE A SEAT, DINK.

15:10.542 --> 15:14.875
(clicking continues)

15:14.917 --> 15:17.458
OKAY.

15:17.500 --> 15:19.792
WHAT THE HELL YOU DOING?

15:19.834 --> 15:23.125
UH, I'M NOT SURE
I UNDERSTAND--

15:23.166 --> 15:25.750
YOU HAVE A WIFE AND A CHILD,
AND YOU'RE NEVER AROUND.

15:25.792 --> 15:28.291
NOW I UNDERSTAND
IT CAN BE DIFFICULT

15:28.333 --> 15:30.291
ONCE THE EXCITEMENT
OF THE BIRTH WEARS OFF,

15:30.333 --> 15:33.208
BUT HEY, MAN, THIS IS--THIS IS
WHEN THE REAL WORK STARTS.

15:33.250 --> 15:36.542
I'M NOT AFRAID
OF HARD WORK.
WELL, THEN
WHY AREN'T YOU THERE?

15:36.583 --> 15:39.208
WHENEVER YOU'RE A NO-SHOW
FOR YOUR NEW FAMILY,

15:39.250 --> 15:41.208
NAOMI ENDS UP
CALLING ME FOR HELP,

15:41.250 --> 15:43.041
AND I'M HAPPY TO DO IT,

15:43.083 --> 15:46.417
BUT QUITE FRANKLY, I'M GETTING
TIRED OF COVERING FOR YOU.

15:46.458 --> 15:48.834
YEAH, IT'S JUST...
(sighs)

15:48.875 --> 15:52.291
IT'S JUST WHAT?

15:52.333 --> 15:54.083
I GOTTA GO.

15:56.333 --> 15:59.041
YES, THE FATHER CARRIES AROUND
ALMOST UNBEARABLE GUILT,

15:59.083 --> 16:01.250
AND, YES, THE MOTHER
HAS COMPENSATED

16:01.291 --> 16:04.333
BY ESSENTIALLY
SHUTTING DOWN EMOTIONALLY.
BUT YOU STILL THINK THAT
THEY SHOULD BE PARENTS AGAIN?

16:04.375 --> 16:06.333
WELL, THEY'RE STRUGGLING TO
ACCEPT A MAJOR TRAGEDY,

16:06.375 --> 16:09.333
BUT I-I DON'T THINK THEY'RE
UNREALISTIC ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

16:09.375 --> 16:12.041
THEY'VE GRIEVED.
IT'S BEEN TWO YEARS, OKAY?

16:12.083 --> 16:14.667
I'M JUST NOT SURE WHAT
THE MARGINAL BENEFIT WOULD BE

16:14.709 --> 16:17.041
TO MAKING THEM WAIT
TO START THEIR LIVES AGAIN.

16:17.083 --> 16:19.041
STOP TRYING TO JUSTIFY THIS
TO ME, OKAY?

16:19.083 --> 16:22.041
IT'S YOUR PRACTICE,
YOUR PATIENTS.
THEY NEED YOUR HELP, ADDISON.

16:22.083 --> 16:24.583
THE SURROGATE HAS SIGNIFICANT
SCARRING OF HER UTERUS

16:24.625 --> 16:26.750
SECONDARY TO INSTRUMENTATION
AFTER A POSTPARTUM HEMORRHAGE.

16:26.792 --> 16:29.583
NO. I'M NOT GETTING INVOLVED.
YOU'RE THE ONLY DOCTOR

16:29.625 --> 16:31.500
IN THIS HALF OF THE COUNTRY
WHO CAN HELP THEM.

16:31.542 --> 16:33.500
THEY'LL NEVER FIND
ANOTHER SURROGATE.

16:33.542 --> 16:36.291
THEY'LL NEVER BE ALLOWED
TO ADOPT.
HOW MUCH DO THEY NEED
TO SUFFER, ADDISON?

16:36.333 --> 16:38.583
AND I'M NOT BAITING YOU.
I'M REALLY ASKING.

16:38.625 --> 16:41.041
I'M NOT SURE IF THAT HUSBAND
OR THAT WIFE ARE EVER

16:41.083 --> 16:44.041
GONNA BE ABLE TO HEAL COMPLETELY
UNTIL THEY GET ANOTHER CHANCE,

16:44.083 --> 16:46.041
AND EVEN THEN,
THERE ARE NO GUARANTEES.

16:46.083 --> 16:48.583
BUT I THINK THEY DESERVE
A SHOT.

16:48.625 --> 16:52.041
DR. BENNETT SAID THAT MY KIDNEY
IS THE RIGHT ONE FOR RYAN.

16:52.083 --> 16:54.792
HOW GOOD'S THE MATCH?
6 OUT OF 6 ALLELES.

16:54.834 --> 16:56.500
HAVE A SEAT, KEVIN.

16:56.542 --> 16:58.500
I WANT TO HELP RYAN.

16:58.542 --> 17:00.041
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

17:00.083 --> 17:03.041
IF YOU GET SICK THE SAME WAY
RYAN IS, IT'LL BE A PROBLEM.

17:03.083 --> 17:05.041
THEN RYAN WILL HELP ME.

17:05.083 --> 17:07.041
I MEAN, HE'LL GIVE ME
HIS KIDNEY.

17:07.083 --> 17:09.041
IT DOESN'T WORK LIKE THAT.

17:09.083 --> 17:11.583
RYAN CAN'T GIVE YOU
HIS KIDNEY.
BUT HE WOULD.

17:11.625 --> 17:15.542
I MEAN, HE WOULD DO IT FOR ME
LIKE I WOULD DO IT FOR HIM.

17:15.583 --> 17:17.417
BROTHERS HELP EACH OTHER.

17:17.458 --> 17:19.125
RIGHT, DR. BENNETT?

17:19.166 --> 17:21.041
YEAH.

17:21.083 --> 17:23.041
THEY DO.

17:23.083 --> 17:26.041
I UNDERSTAND HOW MUCH
YOU WANT TO HELP YOUR BROTHER.

17:26.083 --> 17:29.625
BUT WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
HE DID ANYTHING FOR YOU?

17:29.667 --> 17:31.041
WELL, HE'S REALLY BUSY.

17:31.083 --> 17:33.208
HE'S GOT A JOB,
AND I DON'T.

17:33.250 --> 17:35.375
IT'S OKAY
THAT YOU DON'T HAVE A JOB.

17:38.208 --> 17:42.041
MAYBE MY JOB
IS TO HELP RYAN?

17:46.458 --> 17:48.625
(elevator bell dings)

17:48.667 --> 17:50.625
DOES THE MAID OF HONOR
USUALLY MAKE A TOAST?

17:50.667 --> 17:53.041
USUALLY RIGHT AFTER HE HELPS
BUSTLE THE BRIDE'S DRESS.

17:53.083 --> 17:55.041
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU CAN THINK IT'S LAME,

17:55.083 --> 17:58.834
BUT IT'S A BIG DEAL.
IT'S--IT'S A WEIRD BIG DEAL.

17:58.875 --> 18:00.667
SHE'S TAKING ADVANTAGE
OF YOU.

18:00.709 --> 18:03.583
SHE'S NOT TAKING--WE HAVE
THAT KIND OF RELATIONSHIP.

18:03.625 --> 18:06.000
IT'S... SPECIAL.
(ding)

18:06.041 --> 18:09.041
WHAT'S VIOLET DO FOR YOU?

18:09.083 --> 18:13.458
SHE KNOWS ME
AND WHY I DO WHAT I DO.

18:13.500 --> 18:15.500
I CAN TALK TO VIOLET
ABOUT ANYTHING,

18:15.542 --> 18:18.417
AND AFTER I DO,
I KNOW WE'RE GONNA BE OKAY.
WELL, I'M GLAD TO HEAR
YOU AND VIOLET

18:18.458 --> 18:21.041
HAVE THIS THING TOGETHER
THAT MAKES YOU SO DAMN HAPPY.

18:21.083 --> 18:23.208
CALL ME CRAZY, BUT I FIGURED
YOU JUST DECIDED

18:23.250 --> 18:26.291
YOU WANTED TO MARRY ME
BECAUSE I WAS THAT PERSON.
WE'RE--WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF AN ARGUMENT.

18:26.333 --> 18:29.291
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
(sighs) I'M GETTING READY
TO HELP YANK THE KIDNEY

18:29.333 --> 18:32.333
OUT OF A MENTALLY RETARDED GUY
WHO DOESN'T KNOW ANY BETTER.

18:32.375 --> 18:35.000
I'M A HUMANITARIAN.
DIDN'T YOU KNOW THAT?

18:39.083 --> 18:41.041
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

18:41.083 --> 18:43.959
I... CAME UP FOR BREAKFAST.

18:44.000 --> 18:45.959
DID IT BELONG
TO SOMEONE ELSE?

18:46.000 --> 18:48.041
BECAUSE YOU LOOK GUILTY.

18:48.083 --> 18:50.750
I'M AVOIDING SOMEONE.
UH, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

18:50.792 --> 18:52.750
I GOT BORED
HANGING AROUND ADDISON'S.

18:52.792 --> 18:55.125
I WAS KIND OF HOPING A PATIENT
WOULD STROKE OUT

18:55.166 --> 18:57.458
OR BANG THEIR SKULL
AGAINST SOMETHING

18:57.500 --> 19:00.375
SO I'D HAVE A CHANCE
TO CUT OPEN THEIR HEAD.
IF IT WERE ANYONE
BUT YOU SAYING THAT,

19:00.417 --> 19:03.083
I'D BE RECOMMENDING THERAPY.
(laughs)
SO WHO YOU HIDING FROM?

19:03.125 --> 19:05.959
CHARLOTTE.
OH, BECAUSE SHE PICKED COOPER?

19:06.000 --> 19:08.125
I'M MAD, WHICH IS...
COMPLETELY REASONABLE.

19:08.166 --> 19:09.750
DON'T YOU THINK?

19:09.792 --> 19:11.125
YOU'RE THE SHRINK.

19:11.166 --> 19:13.125
WE'RE NOTORIOUSLY BAD
AT SELF-ANALYSIS,

19:13.166 --> 19:16.959
BUT EVERY TIME I SEE CHARLOTTE,
I WANNA... PUNCH A PUPPY.

19:17.000 --> 19:18.583
(elevator bell dings)

19:18.625 --> 19:20.333
SHE SCREWED YOU, SHELDON.

19:20.375 --> 19:24.542
SHE DITCHED YOU FOR ANOTHER MAN.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO LET IT GO.
WELL, I-I JUST--

19:24.583 --> 19:26.333
WHY HIDE YOUR FEELINGS?
YOU WORK HERE.

19:26.375 --> 19:28.166
WALK AROUND
WITH YOUR HEAD HELD HIGH

19:28.208 --> 19:31.875
AND SAY
TO HELL WITH CHARLOTTE KING.
(clicks buttons)

19:34.583 --> 19:37.000
I'M NOT A BAD GUY, DR. KING.

19:37.041 --> 19:38.542
I JUST...

19:38.583 --> 19:40.542
YOU KNOW,
I SPENT MY WHOLE LIFE

19:40.583 --> 19:44.125
WATCHING MY PARENTS
SO FOCUSED ON KEVIN.

19:44.166 --> 19:47.041
IT WAS ALWAYS ABOUT HIM.

19:47.083 --> 19:49.917
I JUST HAD... ME.

19:49.959 --> 19:51.583
I'M SURE
IT MUST HAVE BEEN DIFFICULT.

19:51.625 --> 19:53.041
WHEN THEY DIED,

19:53.083 --> 19:55.166
I WAS IN THE MIDDLE
OF BUILDING A BUSINESS,

19:55.208 --> 19:57.792
OF BUILDING A LIFE
FOR MYSELF.

19:57.834 --> 20:00.792
I COULDN'T TAKE CARE OF HIM
THE WAY HE NEEDS.

20:00.834 --> 20:03.000
WE BOTH WOULD'VE BEEN
WORSE OFF.

20:04.458 --> 20:07.375
AFTER A WHILE,
I HAD MY LIFE,

20:07.417 --> 20:10.208
HE HAD HIS.

20:10.250 --> 20:14.000
THINK ABOUT WHAT HE'S DOING
FOR YOU NOW.

20:14.041 --> 20:17.000
LET'S GET HIM PREPPED.

20:19.250 --> 20:22.041
IS THIS LOW BACK SEXY

20:22.083 --> 20:26.041
OR A LITTLE HOOCHIE?

20:26.083 --> 20:27.792
RIGHT.
IT'S A LITTLE HOOCHIE.

20:27.834 --> 20:30.041
THEN THERE'S THIS ONE,
WHICH IS, UM...

20:30.083 --> 20:31.458
(unzips zipper)

20:31.500 --> 20:33.041
VERY, VERY BEAUTIFUL,

20:33.083 --> 20:35.250
BUT DO YOU THINK
I CAN CARRY OFF

20:35.291 --> 20:37.000
A BOW AT THE BUST?

20:39.250 --> 20:41.417
COOPER?
I CAN'T DO WEDDING STUFF
RIGHT NOW.

20:41.458 --> 20:43.417
OKAY. WELL, I HAVE TO PUT ON

20:43.458 --> 20:46.041
ONE OF THESE DRESSES
IN THE NEXT 24 HOURS,

20:46.083 --> 20:49.041
SO WHEN EXACTLY
DO YOU WANT TO DO IT?
WHY DO I HAVE TO DO IT AT ALL?

20:49.083 --> 20:51.041
WAIT.
AM I--AM I TALKING TO,

20:51.083 --> 20:54.208
UH, OBJECTIVE COOPER
OR FRIEND COOPER RIGHT NOW?
(sighs)

20:54.250 --> 20:57.208
FRIEND COOPER WOULD SAY,
SKIP THE BOW.

20:57.250 --> 20:59.125
OBJECTIVE COOPER WOULD SAY,

20:59.166 --> 21:01.834
SKIP THE WEDDING.
STILL?

21:01.875 --> 21:04.834
WOW. YOU CAN'T GET THESE GUYS
ON THE SAME PAGE, HUH?

21:04.875 --> 21:07.041
I'M WORKING ON IT.

21:07.083 --> 21:10.417
H-HOW WELL DO YOU THINK
YOU KNOW PETE?

21:10.458 --> 21:12.417
UM... WELL, LET'S SEE.

21:12.458 --> 21:14.041
WE, UH...

21:14.083 --> 21:16.041
WE CONCEIVED
A CHILD TOGETHER,

21:16.083 --> 21:19.125
AND THEN WENT THROUGH A--
OKAY. WERE YOU SURPRISED
WHEN HE PROPOSED?

21:19.166 --> 21:21.041
YES.

21:21.083 --> 21:23.250
BUT IT WAS
A GOOD SURPRISE.

21:23.291 --> 21:26.750
THIS TIME.

21:26.792 --> 21:30.125
ARE YOU REALLY
THAT WORRIED ABOUT ME?

21:30.166 --> 21:33.041
AND US.

21:33.083 --> 21:35.041
EVEN AFTER YOU AND PETE
GET MARRIED,

21:35.083 --> 21:38.041
I STILL WANT US TO BE US.

21:38.083 --> 21:39.750
WELL, THAT WILL NEVER CHANGE,

21:39.792 --> 21:42.792
EVER.

21:45.041 --> 21:47.000
HEY, ADDIE.
HAVE YOU GOT A SECOND?

21:47.041 --> 21:49.709
YEAH. WALK WITH ME.
HI, SAM.

21:49.750 --> 21:51.750
HEY, AMELIA.

21:51.792 --> 21:54.083
HELLO, ADDISON.

21:54.125 --> 21:56.500
HELLO.

21:56.542 --> 22:00.375
OKAY, WELL, I GOTTA GET BACK
TO THE HOSPITAL, SO...

22:00.417 --> 22:03.000
WHAT EXACTLY WENT ON
BETWEEN THE TWO OF YOU?

22:03.041 --> 22:05.041
BECAUSE THAT MOJO IS BAD.
(laughs)

22:05.083 --> 22:06.959
YOU WANTED SOMETHING,
AMELIA?

22:07.000 --> 22:08.417
YES. I TRIED CALLING DEREK.

22:08.458 --> 22:10.417
ACTUALLY,
I CALLED AND E-MAILED.

22:10.458 --> 22:12.500
HE'S IGNORING ME,
SO THE ONLY WAY

22:12.542 --> 22:14.542
I CAN FIND OUT HOW HE'S DOING
IS TO CALL MY MOTHER,

22:14.583 --> 22:17.125
WHO LECTURES ME ON HOW
I SHOULD CALL MY BROTHER,

22:17.166 --> 22:19.125
WHICH MEANS
I HAVE TO GET OFF THE PHONE

22:19.166 --> 22:21.542
BEFORE I FIND OUT
HOW HE'S DOING.
HE'S DOING FINE.

22:21.583 --> 22:24.041
WAIT, YOU'VE HEARD
FROM HIM?

22:24.083 --> 22:26.125
YES, AMELIA. I--

22:26.166 --> 22:28.792
WELL, THAT KINDA SAYS IT ALL,
DOESN'T IT?

22:32.667 --> 22:35.417
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

22:35.458 --> 22:37.041
HOW DID IT GO?

22:37.083 --> 22:38.458
SMOOTHLY.

22:38.500 --> 22:40.458
YOUR NEW KIDNEY
STARTED WORKING RIGHT AWAY.

22:40.500 --> 22:42.458
YOU'RE GONNA BE A BIT SORE,

22:42.500 --> 22:45.041
BUT WE'LL HAVE YOU
ON YOUR FEET IN NO TIME.

22:45.083 --> 22:48.041
WH--OH.
WHAT ABOUT KEVIN? IS HE OKAY?

22:48.083 --> 22:50.667
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU
ASK HIM YOURSELF?

22:50.709 --> 22:54.792
(beeping continues)

22:54.834 --> 22:58.458
HEY. DID IT WORK?
DID I HELP?

22:58.500 --> 23:01.041
YEAH. IT WORKED.

23:01.083 --> 23:02.792
YOU SAVED ME, BUDDY.

23:02.834 --> 23:04.166
I'M NEVER GONNA FORGET IT.

23:04.208 --> 23:06.917
I KNEW I COULD, RYAN.

23:06.959 --> 23:08.792
I KNEW IT.

23:08.834 --> 23:11.625
(beeping continues)

23:11.667 --> 23:15.041
IT'S GONNA BE DIFFERENT NOW.
I'M GONNA BE DIFFERENT.

23:15.083 --> 23:17.041
I'M HAPPY TO HEAR IT.

23:17.083 --> 23:19.417
HOW BAD IS THE SCARRING?

23:19.458 --> 23:22.041
(Dave) THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU CAN DO, RIGHT?

23:22.083 --> 23:24.834
SHARON REALLY WANTS
TO BE OUR SURROGATE.
MR. AND MRS. WALKER,

23:24.875 --> 23:27.417
WOULD YOU MIND GIVING ME
A MOMENT ALONE WITH SHARON?

23:33.917 --> 23:36.041
YOU CAN'T FIX ME, CAN YOU?

23:36.083 --> 23:38.667
I'D HAVE TO DO A HYSTEROSCOPY
AND RESECT THE SCAR,

23:38.709 --> 23:40.500
BUT, YES, I CAN.

23:40.542 --> 23:42.041
THAT'S--THAT'S GREAT.

23:42.083 --> 23:45.041
BUT THERE ARE RISKS--BLEEDING,
A PERFORATION, FURTHER INJURY.

23:45.083 --> 23:47.041
AND UNLESS YOU'RE INTENT
ON HAVING ANOTHER CHILD,

23:47.083 --> 23:49.041
THERE'S NO REASON THAT YOU
SHOULD TAKE THOSE RISKS.

23:49.083 --> 23:51.542
I REALLY WANT TO HAVE
A BABY FOR THE WALKERS.

23:51.583 --> 23:54.458
ARE YOU ESPECIALLY CLOSE
TO THEM?

23:54.500 --> 23:56.041
WE JUST MET.

23:56.083 --> 23:58.750
SO ARE YOU DOING IT
FOR THE MONEY?
NO.

23:58.792 --> 24:00.417
THEN MAY I ASK

24:00.458 --> 24:03.041
WHY YOU'RE SO INTERESTED
IN HELPING THEM?

24:03.083 --> 24:08.041
BECAUSE I KNOW
WHAT THEY'RE GOING THROUGH.

24:08.083 --> 24:11.041
I LOST A CHILD, TOO,

24:11.083 --> 24:13.458
THE SAME WAY.

24:17.500 --> 24:19.792
IT'S A HORROR SHOW.

24:19.834 --> 24:22.583
THAT MAYBE WE COULD MAKE
A LITTLE LESS HORRIFIC.

24:22.625 --> 24:26.083
WHY ARE YOU SO INTENT
ON HELPING THESE PEOPLE?
BECAUSE I HAVE TO BELIEVE
IN STARTING OVER.

24:26.125 --> 24:28.041
THERE'S ALWAYS
A POSSIBILITY.

24:28.083 --> 24:30.458
LOOK, ADDISON,
IT IS A CRAPPY WORLD--

24:30.500 --> 24:32.959
AMELIA SAID THAT--
BUT I CAN'T LIVE WITH THAT.

24:33.000 --> 24:37.250
WITH DELL AND--AND MAYA
AND WILLIAM AND DEREK--

24:37.291 --> 24:40.583
THERE HAS TO BE
A FLIP SIDE TO CRAPPY.

24:40.625 --> 24:42.583
WHY WON'T YOU HELP THEM?

24:42.625 --> 24:45.750
NAOMI, COULD WE HAVE
A MINUTE, PLEASE?

24:52.166 --> 24:55.041
I WAS THERE, SHELDON,
THAT DAY IN THE E.R.

24:55.083 --> 24:56.792
IT WAS UNBEARABLE.

24:56.834 --> 24:59.333
THE FATHER WAS DESTROYED,
THE MOTHER LOST EVERYTHING--

24:59.375 --> 25:01.417
HER BABY AND HER FAITH
IN HER HUSBAND.

25:01.458 --> 25:03.709
I MEAN, HOW CAN THEY
POSSIBLY MOVE PAST THAT?

25:03.750 --> 25:05.542
AND THEY'RE BOTH COMING FROM
THESE TERRIBLE PLACES,

25:05.583 --> 25:07.333
MOVING AS FAST AS THEY CAN,

25:07.375 --> 25:09.125
TRYING TO LEAVE
THE PAST BEHIND THEM

25:09.166 --> 25:11.166
BY MAKING THIS HUGE COMMITMENT,
AND--

25:11.208 --> 25:14.792
I WAS WONDERING WHY YOU WERE
SO EMOTIONAL ABOUT THIS.
WELL, I JUST TOLD YOU.

25:14.834 --> 25:17.542
NO, ADDISON, I'VE SPENT ENOUGH
TIME IN THE ELEVATOR WITH YOU

25:17.583 --> 25:20.291
TO KNOW THAT THIS ABOUT MORE
THAN MUST THE WALKERS.
NO, DON'T SHRINK ME, SHELDON.

25:20.333 --> 25:22.291
IT DOESN'T REQUIRE
A LOT OF SHRINKING.

25:22.333 --> 25:25.417
PEOPLE COMING FROM BAD PLACES,
JUMPING INTO SOMETHING FAST.

25:25.458 --> 25:27.041
N-NO, NO.

25:27.083 --> 25:29.583
PETE CHOSE VIOLET,
YOU CHOSE SAM,

25:29.625 --> 25:31.417
WHICH I REALIZE
THAT I ENCOURAGED.

25:31.458 --> 25:33.417
IN ANY EVENT,
PETE AND VIOLET WORKED OUT,

25:33.458 --> 25:35.792
YOU AND SAM DIDN'T.
NOW THEY'RE GETTING MARRIED,

25:35.834 --> 25:39.792
AND... AND YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT'S IN A BAD PLACE.

25:39.834 --> 25:41.375
I'M FINE.

25:41.417 --> 25:44.375
YOU WILL BE. BUT THE WALKERS?
THEY'RE FINE RIGHT NOW.

25:44.417 --> 25:47.000
GIVE THEM A CHANCE, ADDISON.

25:52.083 --> 25:55.166
I'M GOOD AT MY JOB.

25:55.208 --> 25:58.041
WELL, I WAS GONNA ASK
HOW EVERYONE'S FEELING,

25:58.083 --> 26:00.792
BUT I THINK THE BETTER
QUESTION IS, WHO'S WINNING?

26:00.834 --> 26:03.208
WE'RE NOT EXACTLY THERE YET.
RYAN'S TEACHING ME
HOW TO PLAY.

26:03.250 --> 26:05.083
(whispers indistinctly)

26:05.125 --> 26:07.458
YEAH.
LIKE THIS?

26:07.500 --> 26:09.083
MM-HMM.
ANOTHER ONE?

26:09.125 --> 26:11.041
HEY.
KING ME.

26:11.083 --> 26:14.667
YOU HEARD THE MAN.
KING HIM.
ONCE WE GET ALL BETTER,
RYAN AND ME,

26:14.709 --> 26:18.041
WE'RE GONNA PLAY TOGETHER
ALL THE TIME.
YOU TWO ARE GONNA HAVE
A REGULAR CHECKERS DATE?

26:18.083 --> 26:20.709
YEAH, WE'RE GONNA PLAY
ALL THE TIME AT RYAN'S HOUSE.

26:20.750 --> 26:22.250
IT'S REALLY BIG.
MM.

26:22.291 --> 26:25.041
YEAH. THERE'S A POOL.
SOUNDS LIKE HE HAS BIG PLANS

26:25.083 --> 26:28.041
FOR YOUR FUTURE TOGETHER.
HE'S GETTING
A LITTLE AHEAD OF HIMSELF.

26:28.083 --> 26:29.709
YEAH. HE MUST BE CRAZY

26:29.750 --> 26:31.750
TO THINK YOU'D PUT YOURSELF
OUT FOR HIM

26:31.792 --> 26:33.750
AFTER WHAT HE DID FOR YOU.

26:33.792 --> 26:35.458
OH! (chuckles)

26:35.500 --> 26:37.875
DR. KING, RYAN...

26:37.917 --> 26:39.834
SAID THAT I COULD DRIVE
HIS CONVERTIBLE.

26:39.875 --> 26:42.291
HOLD ON. I DIDN'T SAY YOU COULD
DRIVE THE CONVERTIBLE.

26:42.333 --> 26:45.667
NO.
I SAID WE WOULD GO DRIVING
IN THE CONVERTIBLE.

26:45.709 --> 26:48.834
NO. (laughs) YOU--YOU SAID THAT
I COULD DRIVE THE CONVERTIBLE.
AAH! OH!

26:48.875 --> 26:51.125
KEVIN, SIT DOWN.
AH!

26:51.166 --> 26:53.125
SIT DOWN!
AAH! OH!

26:53.166 --> 26:55.458
(Kevin) WHAT DID I DO?
YOU'RE BLEEDING
INTO YOUR ABDOMEN.

26:55.500 --> 26:58.125
I NEED SOME HELP IN HERE!
I'M SORRY. WHAT DID I DO?

26:58.166 --> 27:00.542
GET HIM OUTTA HERE.
WHAT DID I DO?

27:00.583 --> 27:03.041
TAKE HIM BACK TO HIS ROOM. GO.
I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY. WHAT HAPPENED?

27:03.083 --> 27:05.667
WHAT DID I DO?
WHAT DID I DO?
(Ryan groaning)

27:05.709 --> 27:07.625
WHAT DID I DO?!

27:11.959 --> 27:13.917
SO I TALKED
TO THE FLOWER LADY,

27:13.959 --> 27:17.917
AND, UH, I HAVE TO LEAVE
A MESSAGE FOR THE CAKE PEOPLE.
I DID THAT LAST NIGHT.

27:17.959 --> 27:20.917
OH. I'M GONNA HAVE TO GET
A MANI-PEDI LATER.
I'M GONNA HAVE A DRINK
WITH SAM TONIGHT

27:20.959 --> 27:22.291
AND JUST SHOW UP TOMORROW.

27:22.333 --> 27:25.291
I GUESS WE HAVE TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT WE'RE DOING WITH LUCAS.

27:25.333 --> 27:27.166
MM-HMM.

27:27.208 --> 27:29.083
(laughs)
DOES IT EVER OCCUR TO YOU

27:29.125 --> 27:30.709
THAT WE'RE
DOING EVERYTHING BACKWARDS?

27:30.750 --> 27:33.041
BABY FIRST, WEDDING SECOND.
YEAH. I MEAN, TECHNICALLY,

27:33.083 --> 27:35.500
I'VE NEVER ACTUALLY BEEN
ON A DATE WITH YOU.
I'LL TAKE YOU ON A DATE

27:35.542 --> 27:38.959
IF I CAN MAKE OUT WITH YOU
IN MY CAR AFTER.
NO, I'M SERIOUS.
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO DATE FIRST,

27:39.000 --> 27:42.041
AND THEN THAT'S HOW
YOU GET TO KNOW SOMEONE.
WE KNOW EACH OTHER.

27:42.083 --> 27:44.959
SO YOU'RE NOT WORRIED ABOUT
SPENDING FOREVER WITH ME?

27:45.000 --> 27:48.125
NOT REALLY.
'CAUSE WE'RE JUST KINDA
JUMPING INTO THIS.

27:48.166 --> 27:51.125
LOOK, YOU CAN NEVER KNOW
EVERYTHING ABOUT SOMEONE,

27:51.166 --> 27:53.041
BUT ABOUT ME?

27:53.083 --> 27:54.792
YOU KNOW ENOUGH.

28:05.417 --> 28:08.333
RELAX.

28:08.375 --> 28:10.041
IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.

28:12.208 --> 28:14.125
(boy) OVER HERE!

28:14.166 --> 28:16.208
(indistinct shouting)

28:16.250 --> 28:18.625
DINK. SCHOOL'S OVER.

28:18.667 --> 28:21.417
HOW COME YOU'RE NOT HOME
WITH MAYA AND OLIVIA?

28:21.458 --> 28:24.583
WE'RE KIND OF IN THE MIDDLE
OF A GAME HERE, BRO.
YOUR GAME'S KINDA OVER, BRO.

28:24.625 --> 28:26.375
DUDE.

28:26.417 --> 28:28.375
GET LOST.

28:28.417 --> 28:31.625
YOU BETTER
GET OUT MY FACE.

28:31.667 --> 28:33.375
(girl) READY. OKAY.

28:33.417 --> 28:36.041
MRS. BENNETT IS DIFFERENT THAN
YOU. SHE DOESN'T WANT ME AROUND.

28:36.083 --> 28:38.375
SO WHAT? WHAT?
YEAH, SO SHE'S ALWAYS
IN MY FACE,

28:38.417 --> 28:41.041
TELLING ME
I'M DOING THINGS WRONG.

28:41.083 --> 28:43.583
THEN SHE JUST TELLS ME
TO GO HOME.

28:43.625 --> 28:45.291
ALL RIGHT. LET'S PLAY.

28:45.333 --> 28:48.208
IT'S NOT THAT I DON'T WANT
TO SEE MAYA AND OLIVIA. I DO.

28:48.250 --> 28:50.208
I THINK ABOUT THEM
ALL THE TIME.

28:50.250 --> 28:51.917
(Sharon Jones &amp; The Dap-Kings)
♪ MAMA, MAMA, MAMA ♪

28:51.959 --> 28:53.083
(grunts)

28:53.125 --> 28:55.375
YOUR EX WIFE--SHE'S SCARY.

28:55.417 --> 28:58.875
WELL, YOU THINK YOU HAVE TO
TELL ME THAT? (chuckles)

28:58.917 --> 29:01.291
I LOVE MAYA AND OLIVIA.

29:01.333 --> 29:03.291
SURE YOU DO.

29:03.333 --> 29:04.291
(grunts)

29:04.333 --> 29:06.625
THAT'S A FOUL. COME ON.

29:06.667 --> 29:10.041
PLAY BALL.

29:10.083 --> 29:13.417
♪ OOH ♪
♪ HE DON'T ALWAYS ACT RIGHT ♪

29:13.458 --> 29:16.041
♪ DOO, DOO, DO-DO-DOO ♪

29:16.083 --> 29:17.166
(grunts)

29:17.208 --> 29:19.125
WHAT WAS THAT?

29:19.166 --> 29:21.041
♪ DON'T YOU KNOW... ♪

29:21.083 --> 29:22.458
GET UP.

29:22.500 --> 29:24.125
♪ HE TREATS ME RIGHT ♪
♪ DOO, DOO, DO-DO-DOO ♪

29:24.166 --> 29:25.875
♪ NOW LOVING HIM ♪

29:25.917 --> 29:28.542
♪ COULD BE SO EASY ♪

29:28.583 --> 29:31.250
♪ BUT MAMA DON'T LIKE MY MAN ♪

29:31.291 --> 29:33.417
WHOA-HO!

29:33.458 --> 29:36.291
♪ NO, SHE DON'T LIKE MY MAN ♪

29:36.333 --> 29:38.250
(exhales)
WHAT HAPPENED THERE?

29:38.291 --> 29:40.917
I DON'T LIKE
BEING PUSHED AROUND.

29:40.959 --> 29:42.500
RIGHT.
YOU PUSHED BACK.

29:42.542 --> 29:44.917
GET IT?

29:46.542 --> 29:48.875
♪ NO, SHE DON'T LIKE MY MAN ♪

29:48.917 --> 29:50.125
(footsteps approach)

29:50.166 --> 29:51.333
HEY.

29:51.375 --> 29:54.500
(exhales deeply)
I'M LEAVING.

29:54.542 --> 29:56.083
YEAH? WHERE TO?

29:56.125 --> 29:58.250
SOMEWHERE NOBODY KNOWS ME,

29:58.291 --> 30:00.333
WHERE I HAVEN'T ALREADY
SCREWED THINGS UP...

30:00.375 --> 30:02.333
WHERE YOU CAN DRINK
IN THE MORNING

30:02.375 --> 30:04.333
AND NOT FEEL GUILTY
ABOUT IT.
(chuckles) YEAH.

30:04.375 --> 30:06.959
WELL, WHEN YOU FIND
A PLACE LIKE THAT, TELL ME.

30:07.000 --> 30:09.375
THAT WOULD
DEFEAT THE PURPOSE.

30:09.417 --> 30:11.375
WELL, NO MATTER
WHERE YOU END UP,

30:11.417 --> 30:13.083
YOU SHOULD START IN SEATTLE.

30:13.125 --> 30:15.083
ADDIE,
WE HAVE BEEN THROUGH THIS.

30:15.125 --> 30:17.750
DEREK DOESN'T WANT TO SEE ME.

30:17.792 --> 30:20.959
GO. DO IT.
AND DON'T LOOK BACK.

30:21.000 --> 30:23.500
I CAN'T.
WHY NOT? WHAT'S THE WORST
THAT'S GONNA HAPPEN?

30:23.542 --> 30:25.959
HE'LL HATE ME.
HE ALREADY HATES YOU.

30:28.125 --> 30:31.208
I'M GONNA START IN SEATTLE.

30:34.542 --> 30:37.041
WHAT HAPPENED?

30:37.083 --> 30:39.500
THE KIDNEY HEMORRHAGED
INTO YOUR ABDOMEN.

30:39.542 --> 30:41.125
HOW BAD IS THAT?

30:41.166 --> 30:43.542
WELL, YOUR BODY
REJECTED THE KIDNEY.

30:43.583 --> 30:46.166
SO WHAT DO WE DO?

30:50.083 --> 30:52.625
(voice breaking) SO...

30:52.667 --> 30:55.041
THAT'S IT?

30:55.083 --> 30:56.792
I'M GONNA DIE?

30:56.834 --> 30:59.542
WE CAN
KEEP YOU COMFORTABLE HERE,

30:59.583 --> 31:03.208
BUT, UM... YES.

31:07.041 --> 31:09.583
WHAT THE HELL
AM I SUPPOSED TO DO NOW?

31:09.625 --> 31:11.041
TELL KEVIN.

31:11.083 --> 31:13.041
TRY TO HELP HIM UNDERSTAND
WHAT'S HAPPENING,

31:13.083 --> 31:14.583
THAT IT'S NOT HIS FAULT.

31:14.625 --> 31:17.625
(crying)

31:17.667 --> 31:19.041
(paper crinkles)

31:19.083 --> 31:20.792
THERE.

31:20.834 --> 31:23.625
I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

31:23.667 --> 31:26.000
SHOULD WE MARRY DADDY?

31:29.041 --> 31:31.000
THANK YOU.

31:33.917 --> 31:35.667
OH.

31:39.917 --> 31:41.291
(elevator bell dings)

31:43.875 --> 31:46.875
I KNOW
WHAT YOU MUST THINK OF US.

31:46.917 --> 31:50.083
I AM... I AM TERRIBLY SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

31:50.125 --> 31:52.083
I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU REMEMBER ME, BUT--

31:52.125 --> 31:54.917
YOU WERE THE ONE WHO TRIED TO
SAVE MAX THAT DAY. I REMEMBER.

31:54.959 --> 31:57.083
I COULDN'T LOOK AT HIM...

31:57.125 --> 31:59.500
MY HUSBAND...

31:59.542 --> 32:02.917
FOR THE LONGEST TIME.

32:02.959 --> 32:05.250
(voice breaks) AND THEN
I COULDN'T LOOK AT MYSELF.

32:05.291 --> 32:08.917
♪♪♪

32:08.959 --> 32:10.834
(sighs)

32:10.875 --> 32:12.834
SO THEN WHY

32:12.875 --> 32:15.417
WOULD YOU WANT TO HAVE
ANOTHER CHILD TOGETHER?

32:15.458 --> 32:17.041
BECAUSE HE'S THE ONLY ONE

32:17.083 --> 32:20.083
WHO UNDERSTANDS
HOW DESPERATE I AM

32:20.125 --> 32:23.208
AND WHAT IT FEELS LIKE
TO HAVE THE WORLD LOOK AT YOU

32:23.250 --> 32:26.041
LIKE... LIKE YOU'RE DAMAGED,

32:26.083 --> 32:28.041
MAYBE BEYOND REPAIR.

32:28.083 --> 32:30.041
BUT THAT'S NOT
HOW YOU SEE YOURSELF.

32:30.083 --> 32:32.750
(man)
♪ AND I'M JUST STANDING HERE ♪

32:32.792 --> 32:35.250
I KNOW I'M NOT
THE SAME PERSON I WAS--

32:35.291 --> 32:38.083
A PERSON
WHO DECORATED THE NURSERY

32:38.125 --> 32:40.667
FOUR MONTHS BEFORE
SHE WAS DUE,

32:40.709 --> 32:45.041
OR BOUGHT BABY CLOTHES
IN BIGGER SIZES TO PUT AWAY,

32:45.083 --> 32:48.375
OR LOOKED FORWARD
TO THE FUTURE.

32:48.417 --> 32:51.333
(sniffles)
THAT ME IS GONE.

32:51.375 --> 32:54.458
BUT IF WE HAD A CHANCE
TO HAVE ANOTHER CHILD...

32:54.500 --> 32:56.041
♪ WAITING ♪

32:56.083 --> 32:57.792
I CAN START OVER.

32:57.834 --> 32:59.166
♪ FOR LOVE TO INTERVENE ♪

32:59.208 --> 33:01.041
AND I'M SCARED.

33:01.083 --> 33:05.041
I'LL ALWAYS BE SCARED,
BUT--BUT I PROMISE YOU,

33:05.083 --> 33:07.083
WE WILL LOVE THAT BABY

33:07.125 --> 33:09.458
AND WE WILL PROTECT
THAT BABY

33:09.500 --> 33:14.208
AND NEVER, EVER
LET ANYTHING HAPPEN.

33:14.250 --> 33:16.166
PLEASE.

33:16.208 --> 33:18.041
I HAVE...

33:18.083 --> 33:22.041
I HAVE ALL THIS LOVE TO GIVE
AND NOWHERE TO PUT IT.

33:22.083 --> 33:24.500
PLEASE.

33:24.542 --> 33:27.583
PLEASE JUST SAY YOU BELIEVE
IN SECOND CHANCES.

33:27.625 --> 33:32.041
♪ OR WASN'T THIS TO BE? ♪

33:34.041 --> 33:37.166
♪ IF I LET GO ♪

33:37.208 --> 33:39.500
I DIDN'T MEAN IT.

33:39.542 --> 33:42.041
I WOULD NEVER DO ANYTHING
TO HURT RYAN.

33:42.083 --> 33:44.291
WHAT HAPPENED
WAS NOT YOUR FAULT.

33:44.333 --> 33:46.375
I TOUCHED HIM,
AND HE GOT SICK.

33:46.417 --> 33:49.041
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG
INSIDE OF RYAN,

33:49.083 --> 33:51.041
PART OF HIM
THAT'S NOT WORKING RIGHT.

33:51.083 --> 33:54.625
BUT THEN I GAVE HIM MY KIDNEY,
AND IT FIXED HIM.

33:54.667 --> 33:58.041
SOMETIMES
THE OPERATIONS THAT WE DO...

33:58.083 --> 33:59.583
DON'T MAKE PEOPLE BETTER.

33:59.625 --> 34:02.041
♪ SAVE ME ♪

34:02.083 --> 34:05.125
♪ 'CAUSE I DON'T WANT... ♪

34:05.166 --> 34:08.542
(crying)
I WANT TO GO HOME, RYAN,

34:08.583 --> 34:10.542
WITH YOU.

34:10.583 --> 34:13.041
I CAN'T GO HOME, BUDDY.

34:13.083 --> 34:15.750
W--NO, I MEAN
ONCE YOU GET BETTER.

34:15.792 --> 34:17.417
I'M NOT GONNA GET BETTER.

34:17.458 --> 34:20.583
♪♪♪

34:20.625 --> 34:22.250
I'M GONNA DIE.

34:22.291 --> 34:24.667
♪ I'M WAITING ♪

34:24.709 --> 34:26.583
YOU'RE NOT OLD.

34:26.625 --> 34:28.583
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE,
KEVIN.

34:28.625 --> 34:30.041
♪ FOR LOVE TO INTERVENE ♪

34:30.083 --> 34:32.250
YOU'RE GONNA GO BACK
TO YOUR OLD LIFE...

34:32.291 --> 34:33.875
NO.

34:33.917 --> 34:35.458
BACK TO YOUR HOME

34:35.500 --> 34:38.041
AND YOUR FRIENDS.

34:38.083 --> 34:40.834
(voice breaking)
I LOVE YOU, KEVIN.

34:40.875 --> 34:42.417
AND I APPRECIATE WHAT...

34:42.458 --> 34:44.208
WHAT YOU DID FOR ME.

34:44.250 --> 34:46.041
♪ FOR LOVE TO INTERVENE ♪

34:46.083 --> 34:48.583
REALLY? YOU DO?
I DO.

34:48.625 --> 34:51.583
AND WHEN I SEE MOM AND DAD
UP IN HEAVEN,

34:51.625 --> 34:55.208
I'M GONNA TELL 'EM
WHAT YOU DID FOR ME.

34:55.250 --> 34:57.917
THEY'RE GONNA BE
SO PROUD OF YOU.

34:57.959 --> 35:01.583
(sniffles)

35:03.792 --> 35:08.041
♪ ANOTHER TRAIN ♪

35:08.083 --> 35:13.000
♪ HAS LEFT THE STATION ♪

35:16.083 --> 35:18.250
HI, DR. BENNETT.

35:18.291 --> 35:20.291
AREN'T YOU SUPPOSED TO BE
GOING TO A WEDDING?

35:20.333 --> 35:23.333
UH, WELL, YEAH. WHAT, DID YOU
THINK I WASN'T GONNA BE HOME?

35:23.375 --> 35:25.333
NO. ACTUALLY, I WAS HOPING
TO CATCH YOU.

35:25.375 --> 35:28.000
MAYA SAID YOU WERE ONLY GOING
FOR THE CEREMONY,

35:28.041 --> 35:31.000
BUT I'M HERE TO TELL YOU TO GO
FOR THE ENTIRE THING, HAVE FUN.

35:31.041 --> 35:32.750
THANK YOU, DINK, BUT, UH--

35:32.792 --> 35:34.125
NO, REALLY, DR. BENNETT.

35:34.166 --> 35:37.458
UH, I'VE GOT IT COVERED.

35:37.500 --> 35:39.041
(exhales)

35:39.083 --> 35:42.041
MAYA IS MY WIFE,
AND OLIVIA IS MY BABY.

35:42.083 --> 35:43.291
DINK--

35:43.333 --> 35:46.417
REALLY, DR. BENNETT,
YOU SHOULD GO GET DRESSED.

36:00.083 --> 36:01.875
NICE JOB.

36:04.125 --> 36:07.125
(string instruments
playing classical music)

36:16.208 --> 36:19.083
(clears throat)

36:19.125 --> 36:21.041
PRETTY.

36:21.083 --> 36:24.041
VERY.

36:24.083 --> 36:26.625
IS THIS WEIRD FOR YOU
AT ALL,

36:26.667 --> 36:28.625
'CAUSE OF VIOLET?

36:28.667 --> 36:31.041
(inhales deeply) W--

36:31.083 --> 36:34.333
I'M FINE WITH IT.

36:34.375 --> 36:36.125
IT'S WEIRD FOR ME.

36:36.166 --> 36:39.041
COOPER WAS PROBABLY BACK THERE
WITH VIOLET JUST NOW

36:39.083 --> 36:43.333
HAVING SOME TEARFUL
FARE-THEE-WELL.

36:43.375 --> 36:46.333
WHAT?
YOU REALLY THINK I SHOULD
BE FEELING SORRY FOR YOU?

36:46.375 --> 36:49.000
YOU GOT ENGAGED TO ANOTHER GUY
WHILE WE WERE ON A DATE.

36:49.041 --> 36:51.166
AND NOW YOU'RE EXPECTING
THAT WE CAN BE FRIENDS,

36:51.208 --> 36:53.792
THAT I CAN BE YOUR CONFIDANT
ABOUT COOPER AND VIOLET.

36:53.834 --> 36:56.125
NO, NO. IT'S NOT... (chuckles)
IT'S NOT HAPPENING,

36:56.166 --> 36:59.041
SO JUST...
FIND ANOTHER FRIEND.

36:59.083 --> 37:03.000
(music continues)

37:10.083 --> 37:12.417
(whispers) HI.

37:14.041 --> 37:17.083
I'M GONNA HELP THE WALKERS.

37:17.125 --> 37:20.250
(Wagner's "Bridal Chorus
from 'Lohengrin'" playing)

37:26.875 --> 37:28.709
(mouths words)

37:28.750 --> 37:32.250
(music continues)

37:38.500 --> 37:41.542
(music continues)

38:00.083 --> 38:01.709
(flowers clatter against object)

38:01.750 --> 38:04.041
HEY. WHAT'S GOING ON?

38:04.083 --> 38:05.917
I'M FREAKING OUT.
THAT'S WHAT'S GOING ON.

38:05.959 --> 38:07.291
ALL RIGHT. LET'S GO.

38:07.333 --> 38:09.291
WE'LL GET IN THE CAR.
WE'LL DRIVE.

38:09.333 --> 38:11.625
WE DON'T HAVE TO STOP TILL
YOU SAY. WE CAN GO ANYWHERE.

38:11.667 --> 38:14.667
WE--WE--WE CAN'T DO THAT,
COOPER.

38:14.709 --> 38:16.458
THAT'S NOT WHAT GROWN-UPS DO.

38:16.500 --> 38:19.041
IS PETE WHO YOU WANT?

38:19.083 --> 38:22.041
IT J--IT JUST ALL HAPPENED
REALLY FAST, YOU KNOW?

38:22.083 --> 38:25.083
AND IT--AND IT'S NOT ABOUT
A DRESS OR A RING OR A PARTY.

38:25.125 --> 38:27.458
IT'S FOREVER. AT LEAST--
AT LEAST IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE.

38:27.500 --> 38:29.458
AND--AND YOU WERE RIGHT.
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

38:29.500 --> 38:32.500
HOW DO YOU KNOW HOW YOU'RE GONNA
FEEL ABOUT SOMEONE FOR FOREVER?

38:32.542 --> 38:34.000
I WAS--

38:37.000 --> 38:40.000
COULD YOU GIVE US A MINUTE?
YEAH, OF COURSE.

39:23.083 --> 39:26.000
(Wilco's "The Thanks I Get"
playing)

39:30.458 --> 39:33.417
♪ IS THAT THE THANKS I GET ♪

39:33.458 --> 39:36.458
♪ FOR LOVING YOU? ♪

39:39.083 --> 39:42.875
♪ YOU SAY YOU WANNA KNOW ♪

39:42.917 --> 39:47.125
♪ WHERE I GO WHEN I GO ♪

